I can make one up for you.

264
00:25:16,481 --> 00:25:18,813
Do you want to tell me a story...

265
00:25:19,184 --> 00:25:21,516
about what happened today at Grandma's?

266
00:25:28,260 --> 00:25:29,818
You go to sleep, honey.

267
00:25:31,396 --> 00:25:33,296
I'll leave the hall light on.

268
00:25:46,378 --> 00:25:47,345
Damn.

269
00:25:51,049 --> 00:25:54,143
No outside calls. You're in isolation.
You know that.

270
00:25:54,252 --> 00:25:56,982
I tried to reach Dr. Raglan. He hasn't come.

271
00:25:57,088 --> 00:25:58,487
He's on his way.

272
00:26:00,292 --> 00:26:01,259
Chris...

273
00:26:04,529 --> 00:26:06,793
Is something wrong? Anything?

274
00:26:09,100 --> 00:26:11,034
Then it's me again.

275
00:26:13,438 --> 00:26:15,565
Nothing's wrong, except with me.

276
00:26:16,341 --> 00:26:20,209
No, that's Frank talking,
Frank twisting my words.

277
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:25,839
He won't be patient, he won't trust me,
he won't wait until I get well.

278
00:26:27,352 --> 00:26:28,614
He thinks...

279
00:26:29,955 --> 00:26:31,752
that I'm turning into my mother.

280
00:26:31,856 --> 00:26:34,950
Day by day, moment by moment,
he thinks that I'm trying...

281
00:26:35,126 --> 00:26:37,651
to make Candy into Baby Nola.

282
00:26:38,029 --> 00:26:39,291
Is he right?

283
00:26:41,866 --> 00:26:45,358
No. That's the last thing on earth I'd...

284
00:26:52,277 --> 00:26:53,369
Who's that?

285
00:26:59,551 --> 00:27:00,643
It's Daddy.

286
00:27:02,687 --> 00:27:05,850
