288
00:27:10,295 --> 00:27:13,389
and I know that he's thinking of a way
to take her away.

289
00:27:14,165 --> 00:27:17,293
And that's very unfair of him.
That's very arrogant of him.

290
00:27:17,402 --> 00:27:20,098
You mustn't be too hard on him,
Nola, sweetheart.

291
00:27:20,305 --> 00:27:23,069
He's just trying to be a good,
protective father.

292
00:27:24,376 --> 00:27:25,400
No.

293
00:27:25,877 --> 00:27:26,935
Yes.

294
00:27:27,345 --> 00:27:30,143
He's just doing
what a good father should do.

295
00:27:30,382 --> 00:27:32,350
He's protecting his little girl.

296
00:27:33,018 --> 00:27:36,681
There's nothing wrong with that, is there?
He doesn't want to see her hurt.

297
00:27:36,788 --> 00:27:40,280
He doesn't want to see her hurt by anybody,
not even her own mother.

298
00:27:40,392 --> 00:27:43,293
Now, is there anything wrong with that?

299
00:27:45,430 --> 00:27:46,397
No.

300
00:27:48,333 --> 00:27:50,096
No, there isn't.

301
00:27:54,239 --> 00:27:57,072
After all, it's just what I did for you, isn't it?

302
00:27:59,344 --> 00:28:03,007
